#DESCRIPTION
Hybrid PIC (kinetic ions / fluid electrons) parallel whistler-Alfven wave test.
Full generalized Ohm's law: convection + Hall + resistive (eta*J) + electron
pressure gradient (grad Pe / (e n_e)) terms ALL active, in normalized CGS units.

Parameters match the Hall-only hybrid_whistler test (same ion-scale
normalization so d_i ~ v_A ~ 1 in code units).  Here RESISTIVITY and
ELECTRONTEMPERATURE are enabled so the complete Ohm's-law field solver is
exercised.  A moderate resistivity damps the whistler, and the electron
pressure gradient acts on the (weak) charge-density fluctuations produced by
particle noise; the test is a STABILITY / no-blow-up regression check for the
full solver, not a dispersion measurement.

#INITFROMSWMF
F                       initFromSWMF

#GEOMETRY
-3.2                    xMin  [code units; Lx = 6.4 d_i]
 3.2                    xMax
-0.05                   yMin
 0.05                   yMax
-0.05                   zMin
 0.05                   zMax

#NCELL
64                      nCellX
1                       nCellY
1                       nCellZ

#MAXBLOCKSIZE
64                      maxBlockSizeX
1                       maxBlockSizeY
1                       maxBlockSizeZ

#PERIODICITY
T                       isPeriodicX
T                       isPeriodicY
T                       isPeriodicZ

#SOLVEEM
F                       solveEM

#HYBRIDPIC
T                       useHybridPIC

#RESISTIVITY
1000000.0               etaResistivity  [m^2/s, SI magnetic diffusivity]

#ELECTRONTEMPERATURE
5.0                     electronTemperature  [eV]
1.0                     electronGamma
1.0                     electronDensity0

#HALLSUBCYCLE
32                      nHallSubcycle   subDt=dt/32=6.25e-4 satisfies Hall CFL dx^2/(6 v_A d_i)

#PLASMA
1                       nSpecies
1.0                     mass        Species 0: kinetic ion (electron is implicit fluid)
1.0                     charge

#UNIFORMSTATE
5.0                     rho [amu/cc]   Species 0: ions (n = 5 /cc)
0.0                     ux [km/s]
0.0                     uy [km/s]
0.0                     uz [km/s]
10000.0                 T [K]
5.2195e-9               bx [T]       uniform guide field Bx0 (B_code ~ 1)
0.0                     by [T]
0.0                     bz [T]
0.0                     ex [V/m]
0.0                     ey [V/m]
0.0                     ez [V/m]

#TESTCASE
HybridWave

#TIMESTEPPING
T                       useFixedDt
0.02                    dt

#NORMALIZATION
1.0e5                   lNormSI   [m]  ~ d_i so d_i ~ 1 in code units
5.0e4                   uNormSI   [m/s] ~ v_A so v_A ~ 1 in code units

#MONITOR
1                       dnReport

#SAVELOG
1                       dnSavePic
1                       dnSavePT

#PARTICLES
2000                    nParticle per cell in X
1                       nParticle per cell in Y
1                       nParticle per cell in Z

#COMOVING
F                       solvePartInCoMov
0                       nSmoothBackGroundU

#UPWINDE
F                       useUpwindE
0.0                     limiterThetaE

#UPWINDB
F                       doSmoothB
0.0                     theta

#SAVEPLOT
1                       nPlot
z=0 fluid ascii pic     plotString
-1                      dn
0.5                     dt
1                       dx
Bx By Bz Ex Ey Ez       varName

#STOP
-1                      MaxIter
6.25                    TimeMax

#RUN
